{"session_id":"svc-1780118502306045451","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-30T05:25:19.512606227Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-helix-c84ecbc5-20260530T052108-3353cc77","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"helix-c84ecbc5\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eINT-DD: DDx integration test — `ddx install` + `ddx work --once` against fixture beads + recording\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nCreate tests/workflows/ddx/ harness that exercises DDx as the reference runtime — install HELIX, file a fixture bead, run one bead-execution, assert the artifacts.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;**Deliverables**:\u0026#xA;- `tests/workflows/ddx/run-scenarios.sh` — orchestrator\u0026#xA;- `tests/workflows/ddx/fixtures/seed-bead.json` — minimal bead spec for SCN-01 bootstrap (sparse intent)\u0026#xA;- `tests/workflows/ddx/expected/` — execution evidence assertions\u0026#xA;- `tests/workflows/ddx/recordings/INT-DD.tape` + `INT-DD.gif`\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;**Harness shape** (reuse `tests/install/ddx/Dockerfile`):\u0026#xA;1. Build image with `ddx` binary\u0026#xA;2. `ddx install helix --local /workspace/helix --force`\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead create \u0026lt;SCN-01-prompt-bead\u0026gt; --type task --priority 1 --description ... --acceptance ...`\u0026#xA;4. `ddx work --once --json \u0026gt; result.json`\u0026#xA;5. Grep result.json for routing decision (`route claude/\u0026lt;model\u0026gt;`) + execution evidence path\u0026#xA;6. Read execution evidence dir; assert vision.md or PRD.md was produced\u0026#xA;7. vhs renders the whole orchestrator\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;**Note**: this also exercises the DDx routing surface that\u0026#39;s been flaky in this session (ddx-a827d07f, ddx-65d3ba51). If the routing fails, the test should fail loudly so we see it.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;context-digest\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;principles\u0026gt;Validate Your Work · Runtime Neutrality · Design for Simplicity\u0026lt;/principles\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;concerns\u0026gt;installer-coverage | screencast-evidence | runtime-parity\u0026lt;/concerns\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;practices\u0026gt;DDx is the reference runtime · test is `ddx install helix --local` then `ddx work --once --json` against fixture beads · assertion: routing decision + execution evidence land · vhs recording of the queue drain\u0026lt;/practices\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;governing\u0026gt;docs/helix/03-test/test-plans/TP-014-helix-workflow-coverage.md SCN-01 (bootstrap) + SCN-06 (review) · docs/install/ddx.md · existing tests/install/ddx/ scaffolding\u0026lt;/governing\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026lt;/context-digest\u0026gt;\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n(Activation here is already behavioral, not prose; this tightens it and adds the negative control.)\u0026#xA;1. `bash tests/workflows/ddx/run-scenarios.sh` exits 0 (with an API key for whatever DDx routes to): installs HELIX (`ddx install helix --local /workspace/helix --force`), creates a fixture SCN-01 bead, runs `ddx work --once --json`.\u0026#xA;2. Activation/behavior assertion (structured — keep): parse result.json for the routing decision (`route \u0026lt;provider\u0026gt;/\u0026lt;model\u0026gt;`) AND assert the execution-evidence dir contains the produced artifact (vision.md or PRD.md). Not a prose grep.\u0026#xA;3. Negative control: running the fixture bead with HELIX NOT installed produces no HELIX routing/artifact and exits NONZERO, proving the assertion depends on the skill.\u0026#xA;4. tests/workflows/ddx/recordings/INT-DD.gif generated via vhs and committed, showing install + bead-create + work-once + evidence inspection. docs/install/README.md (DDx section) links it.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ehelix, phase:test, activity:test, kind:test, area:testing, area:packaging, runtime:ddx\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"helix-e3c7d0e4\" spec-id=\"helix.installer-integration-tests\" base-rev=\"b9da04903a4325f9872008c5b6a7b19a760571f7\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260530T052108-3353cc77\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-helix-c84ecbc5-20260530T052108-3353cc77/.ddx/executions/20260530T052108-3353cc77/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-helix-c84ecbc5-20260530T052108-3353cc77/.ddx/executions/20260530T052108-3353cc77/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/h